><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=noonievioletskies>NoonieVioletskies</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1474<br> <font color=#333333>(12/16/02 6:29:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=418.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  ..</span><hr size=1> You know if mages scaled as much as rogues did, they would have a point. Sorry, balancing a whole class which *does not* scale that well around the bottom of the barrel (it takes like 0 effort to obtain a rb and a lsoee) of another class which is very flexible equipment wise, makes no sense. Yet they expect verant to do this.<br>
